    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1820_05_21_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>  
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Palais-Bourbon-FR">93 Place Bourbon</placeName> <note>136</note>
                        <date when="1820-05-21">May 21.<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> 1820.</date>
                       
                    </dateline></opener>
                <p>
                    I have been at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Passy_FR">Passy</placeName> and our<lb/>
                    dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GautM1" cert="high">Madame Gautier</persName> has read<lb/>
                    to me your kind letter. My dear<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">friend</persName> it gratifies but does not<lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">surprise</hi> me to hear that your<lb/>
                    plans for the summer will depend<lb/>
                    so much upon your kindness<lb/>
                    for us - I hasten to settle at once<lb/>
                    all your doubts as to my projects<lb/>
                    - Unless ill health or some <choice><orig>un-<lb/>
                    foreseen</orig><reg>unforeseen</reg></choice> family misfortune sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi><lb/>
                    prevent me from fulfilling<lb/>
                    my intentions we shall <choice><orig>assured-<lb/>
                    ly</orig><reg>assuredly</reg></choice> be at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Geneva_SZ">Geneva,</placeName> at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Pregny-Chambésy_SZ">Pregny</placeName> with<lb/>
                    our friends <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MoilJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MoilA1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. <choice><orig>Moulliet</orig><reg>Moilliet</reg></choice></persName><lb/>
                    the latter end of July - Whether<lb/>
                    in the 3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> or last week I cannot<lb/>
                    yet determine; but I will write<lb/>
                    again more precisely towards the<lb/>
                
                <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1820_05_21_page02.jpg"/>
                    middle of next month.<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    I must add for my own <choice><orig>justifi<lb/>
                    cation</orig><reg>justification</reg></choice> that I wrote nearly to this<lb/>
                    effect to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Marcet</persName> three days<lb/>
                    after our arrival at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris,</placeName> as I<lb/>
                    was anxious not to leave our<lb/>
                    excellent friends at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Geneva_SZ">Geneva</placeName> &amp;<lb/>
                    yourself in particular in any<lb/>
                    doubt as to our intentions - I<lb/>
                    requested <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> . Marcet</persName> to <choice><orig>commu-<lb/>
                    nicate</orig><reg>communicate</reg></choice> my letter to you my dear<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">Sir</persName> as I was much hurried &amp;<lb/>
                    literally had not time to write<lb/>
                    more than a few lines - I imagine<lb/>
                    that my letter (Though carefully<lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">postpaid</hi>) has never reached its<lb/>
                    destination. This by the hand of<lb/>
                    a private friend will be secure of<lb/>
                    reaching you.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1820_05_21_page03.jpg"/>
                <note>137</note>
                <p>
                    My <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntR1" cert="high">bookseller</persName> writes me word<lb/>
                    that he has according to my <choice><orig>de<lb/>
                    =sire</orig><reg>desire</reg></choice> reserved copies (with <hi rend="underline">proof</hi><lb/>
                    prints) of my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">fathers</persName> <title ref="./Workography.xml#Memoi1">memoirs</title><lb/>
                    for you and for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> . Marcet</persName><lb/>
                    - &amp; that he has sent the books<lb/>
                    to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HaldW1" cert="low">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <choice><orig>Haldiman</orig><reg>Haldimand</reg></choice></persName> to convey to<lb/>
                    you not knowing any better <choice><orig>me-<lb/>
                    =thod</orig><reg>method</reg></choice> of forwarding them.<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    I have just received a copy<lb/>
                    of the <title ref="./Workography.xml#Memoi1">book</title> by the diligence, which<lb/>
                    I have put into the hands of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BuchJ1">M.<lb/>
                    Buchon</persName> to translate. - Several <choice><orig>ap-<lb/>
                    -plied</orig><reg>applied</reg></choice> to me; but I preferred <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BuchJ1">M. <choice><orig>Bu-<lb/>
                    -chon</orig><reg>Buchon</reg></choice></persName> from the specimen he has<lb/>
                    shewn me of his talents in the late<lb/>
                    translation of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StewD1">Stewart's</persName> <title ref="./Workography.xml#Preli1">"Dissertation</title><lb/>
                    in the <title ref="./Workography.xml#Encyc1">Encyclopedia Britannique</title><lb/>
                    - I have this moment seen him<lb/>
                    &amp; he begins on Wednesday - I have<lb/>
                    promised that he shall not <unclear>add</unclear><lb/>
                    <unclear>either</unclear> preface or notes - He <unclear/><lb/>
                
                <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1820_05_21_page04.jpg"/>
                    that many things will require notes<lb/>
                    of explanation to make them intelligible<lb/>
                    or interesting to the French - I engage to<lb/>
                    write these notes -<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    I cannot express to you how anxious I<lb/>
                    feel to hear your opinion of the <title ref="./Workography.xml#Memoi1">book</title><lb/>
                    -from you I know that I shall hear<lb/>
                    the truth &amp; a judgement from which<lb/>
                    in my own &amp; in my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">fathers</persName> opinion<lb/>
                    there is no appeal<lb/></p>
                <closer>
                    Ever, with perfect esteem &amp;<lb/>
                    gratitude your affectionate friend<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/></closer>
                <postscript><p>
                    I forgot to explain that by <hi rend="underline">We</hi> I mean my<lb/>
                    sisters <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Fanny</persName> and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH1">Harriet</persName> &amp; myself - <choice><orig>pre-<lb/>
                    pare</orig><reg>prepare</reg></choice> two warm corners in your heart for these<lb/>
                    dear sisters of mine-<lb/></p></postscript>
                <closer><address>
                <addrLine>a</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Monsieur</addrLine>
                 <addrLine><persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">Mons<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> . Dumont</persName></addrLine>
                 <addrLine>a <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Geneva_SZ">Geneve</placeName> .</addrLine></address></closer>
                
            </div>
        </body>
        <back> </back>
    </text>
